  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, via API gives a peer count of 19:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl http://localhost:5051/network/peer_count\r\n19\r\n```\r\n\r\nVia metrics gives a peer count of 23:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl http://localhost:8008/metrics 2>/dev/null | grep peers\r\n# HELP libp2p_peers Tracks number of libp2p peers\r\n# TYPE libp2p_peers gauge\r\nlibp2p_peers 23.0\r\n# HELP network_peer_goodbye_total Total number of goodbye messages received from peers\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would probably be better to expose something like `beacon_peer_count` via the metrics interface (I'm compiling a list of other ways we can enhance the metrics). I don't know which of these is the more relevant.",
